<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="341" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,572,1210]" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,572,598]" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male body length 22.0 mm. Very large, swollen eyes. Synthlipsis two-thirds narrower than eye. Postocular region two-thirds shorter than eye length. Pronotum piceous. Lateral margin of pronotum with thin but well-developed keel. Humeral angles rounded. Overall color of corium yellow, with dark brown apex and central marks. Membrane of hemelytra light brown. Overall color of connexival segments yellow, with dark brown marking on anterior third of segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,572,1210]" box="[199,530,752,779]" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,454,752,778]" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">Specimens examined.</emphasis>
None.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
