<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="341" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,572,1210]" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,824,850]" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">Comments.</emphasis>
Carcavalho 
<emphasis box="[484,544,824,850]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">et al.</emphasis>
(2000) proposed that 
<taxonomicName authority="Martinez, Carcavallo &amp; Pelaez, 1984" authorityName="Martinez, Carcavallo &amp; Pelaez" authorityYear="1984" box="[805,1400,824,850]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Triatoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brailovskyi">
<emphasis box="[805,960,824,850]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">T. brailovskyi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Martinez, A. &amp; Carcavallo, R. U. &amp; Pelaez, D." box="[971,1400,824,850]" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" pagination="39 - 42" refId="ref23540" refString="Martinez, A., Carcavallo, R. U. &amp; Pelaez, D. (1984) Triatoma brailovskyi, nueva especie de Triatominae en Mexico. Chagas, 1, 39 - 42." type="journal article" year="1984">Martínez, Carcavallo &amp; Pelaez, 1984</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is close to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Latreille" baseAuthorityYear="1811" box="[244,379,860,886]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Triatoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis box="[244,379,860,886]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">T. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Mazzotti, 1940" authorityName="Mazzotti" authorityYear="1940" box="[393,685,860,886]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Triatoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hegneri">
<emphasis box="[393,506,860,886]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">T. hegneri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mazzotti, L." box="[512,685,860,886]" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" pagination="127 - 131" refId="ref24741" refString="Mazzotti, L. (1940). Una especie rara de Triatoma. Triatoma mexicana (H. Schaeffer, 1848). Medicina, Revista Mexicana, 359, 127 - 131." type="journal article" year="1940">Mazzotti, 1940</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Martinez, Carcavallo &amp; Juberg, 1994" authorityName="Martinez, Carcavallo &amp; Juberg" authorityYear="1994" box="[743,1340,860,886]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Triatoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gomeznunezi">
<emphasis box="[743,915,861,886]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">T. gomeznunezi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Martinez, A. &amp; Carcavallo, R. U. &amp; Juberg, J." box="[922,1340,860,886]" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" pagination="15 - 19" refId="ref23577" refString="Martinez, A., Carcavallo, R. U. &amp; Juberg, J. (1994) Triatoma gomeznunezi a new species of Triatomini from Mexico (Hemiptera: Reduviidae: Triatominae). Entomologia y Vectores, 1, 15 - 19." type="journal article" year="1994">Martínez, Carcavallo &amp; Juberg, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, arguing morphological similarities between these species but without details. This statement was followed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schofield, C. J. &amp; Galvao, C." pageId="6" pageNumber="341" pagination="88 - 100" refId="ref26242" refString="Schofield, C. J. &amp; Galvao, C. (2009) Classification, evolution, and species groups within the Triatominae. Acta Tropica, 110, 88 - 100. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. actatropica. 2009.01.010" type="journal article" year="2009">Schofield &amp; Galvão (2009)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Espinoza, B. &amp; Martinez-Ibarra, J. A. &amp; Villalobos, G. &amp; De La Torre, P. &amp; Laclette, J. P. &amp; Martinez-Hernandez, F." box="[366,622,932,958]" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" pagination="275 - 284" refId="ref21725" refString="Espinoza, B., Martinez-Ibarra, J. A., Villalobos, G., De La Torre, P., Laclette, J. P. &amp; Martinez-Hernandez, F. (2013) Genetic variation of North American triatomines (Insecta: Hemiptera: Reduviidae): Initial divergence between species and populations of Chagas disease vector. The American Journal of Tropical Medicine and Hygiene, 88, 275 - 284. https: // doi. org / 10.4269 / ajtmh. 2012.12 - 0105" type="journal article" year="2013">
Espinoza 
<emphasis box="[478,538,932,958]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">et al.</emphasis>
(2013)
</bibRefCitation>
suggested that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martinez, Carcavallo &amp; Pelaez" authorityYear="1984" box="[805,959,932,958]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Triatoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brailovskyi">
<emphasis box="[805,959,932,958]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">T. brailovskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Usinger" authorityYear="1939" box="[1098,1259,932,958]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Triatoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipennis">
<emphasis box="[1098,1259,932,958]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">T. longipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Stal, 1868)" baseAuthorityName="Stal" baseAuthorityYear="1868" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Triatoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recurva">
<emphasis box="[1320,1436,933,958]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">T. recurva</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stal, C." box="[159,279,968,995]" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" pagination="1 - 148" refId="ref26363" refString="Stal, C. (1868) Hemiptera Fabriciana. Pars 1. Heteroptera. Svenska Vetenskapsakademiens Handlingar, 7, 1 - 148." type="journal article" year="1868">Stål, 1868</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
considering phylogenetic relationships. This arrangement was followed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Monteiro, F. A. &amp; Weirauch, C. &amp; Felix, M. &amp; Lazoski, C. &amp; Abad-Franch, F." box="[1169,1432,968,994]" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" pagination="265 - 344" refId="ref25037" refString="Monteiro, F. A., Weirauch, C., Felix, M., Lazoski, C. &amp; Abad-Franch, F. (2018). Evolution, systematics, and biogeography of the Triatominae, vectors of Chagas disease. Advances in Parasitology, 99, 265 - 344. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / bs. apar. 2017.12.002" type="journal article" year="2018">
Monteiro 
<emphasis box="[1284,1344,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
. Consensus information used by 
<bibRefCitation author="Espinoza, B. &amp; Martinez-Ibarra, J. A. &amp; Villalobos, G. &amp; De La Torre, P. &amp; Laclette, J. P. &amp; Martinez-Hernandez, F." box="[515,766,1004,1030]" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" pagination="275 - 284" refId="ref21725" refString="Espinoza, B., Martinez-Ibarra, J. A., Villalobos, G., De La Torre, P., Laclette, J. P. &amp; Martinez-Hernandez, F. (2013) Genetic variation of North American triatomines (Insecta: Hemiptera: Reduviidae): Initial divergence between species and populations of Chagas disease vector. The American Journal of Tropical Medicine and Hygiene, 88, 275 - 284. https: // doi. org / 10.4269 / ajtmh. 2012.12 - 0105" type="journal article" year="2013">
Espinoza 
<emphasis box="[626,684,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">et al.</emphasis>
(2013)
</bibRefCitation>
masked large incongruence between phylogenies based on mitochondrial and nuclear genes in respect of phylogenetic relationships of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martinez, Carcavallo &amp; Pelaez" authorityYear="1984" box="[1039,1194,1040,1066]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Triatoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brailovskyi">
<emphasis box="[1039,1194,1040,1066]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">T. brailovskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Only mitochondrial phylogeny reveals a close relationship between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martinez, Carcavallo &amp; Pelaez" authorityYear="1984" box="[693,846,1076,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Triatoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brailovskyi">
<emphasis box="[693,846,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">T. brailovskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Usinger" authorityYear="1939" box="[912,1072,1076,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Triatoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipennis">
<emphasis box="[912,1072,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">T. longipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stal" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[1128,1243,1077,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Triatoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recurva">
<emphasis box="[1128,1243,1077,1102]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">T. recurva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Instead, nuclear phylogeny shows 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martinez, Carcavallo &amp; Pelaez" authorityYear="1984" box="[353,504,1112,1138]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Triatoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brailovskyi">
<emphasis box="[353,504,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">T. brailovskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the sister taxon of the remaining species of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1067,1223,1112,1138]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Triatoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phyllosoma">
<emphasis box="[1067,1223,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">T. phyllosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group plus 
<taxonomicName authority="(LeConte, 1855) (Espinoza et al. 2013)" authorityName="Espinoza et al." authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="LeConte" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[151,776,1148,1175]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Triatoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguisuga">
<emphasis box="[151,310,1149,1174]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">T. sanguisuga</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="LeConte, J. L." box="[327,499,1148,1175]" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" pagination="404" refId="ref22938" refString="LeConte, J. L. (1855) Remarks on two species of American Cimex. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 7, 404." type="journal article" year="1855">LeConte, 1855</bibRefCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Espinoza, B. &amp; Martinez-Ibarra, J. A. &amp; Villalobos, G. &amp; De La Torre, P. &amp; Laclette, J. P. &amp; Martinez-Hernandez, F." box="[524,768,1148,1174]" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" pagination="275 - 284" refId="ref21725" refString="Espinoza, B., Martinez-Ibarra, J. A., Villalobos, G., De La Torre, P., Laclette, J. P. &amp; Martinez-Hernandez, F. (2013) Genetic variation of North American triatomines (Insecta: Hemiptera: Reduviidae): Initial divergence between species and populations of Chagas disease vector. The American Journal of Tropical Medicine and Hygiene, 88, 275 - 284. https: // doi. org / 10.4269 / ajtmh. 2012.12 - 0105" type="journal article" year="2013">
Espinoza 
<emphasis box="[639,698,1148,1174]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Similar conclusion can be retrieved from ultraconserved elements of molecular data (
<bibRefCitation author="Kieran, T. J. &amp; Gordon, E. R. L. &amp; Zaldivar-Riveron, A. &amp; Ibarra-Cerdena, C. N. &amp; Glenn, T. C. &amp; Weirauch, C." box="[468,676,1184,1210]" pageId="6" pageNumber="341" pagination="725 - 740" refId="ref22645" refString="Kieran, T. J., Gordon, E. R. L., Zaldivar-Riveron, A., Ibarra-Cerdena, C. N., Glenn, T. C. &amp; Weirauch, C. (2021) Ultraconserved elements reconstruct the evolution of Chagas disease-vectoring kissing bugs (Reduviidae: Triatominae). Systematic Entomology, 4 (3), 725 - 740. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12485" type="journal article" year="2021">
Kieran 
<emphasis box="[553,609,1184,1210]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="341">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
